=============================================
Installing ONIE on Inventec Redwood_x86
=============================================

Cross-Compiling ONIE
====================

Change directories to ``build-config`` to compile ONIE.

To compile ONIE first change directories to ``build-config`` and then
type ``"make MACHINEROOT=../machine/inventec MACHINE=redwood_x86 all"``.  For example::

  $ cd build-config
  $ make -j4 MACHINEROOT=../machine/inventec MACHINE=redwood_x86 all recovery-iso

When complete, the ONIE binaries are located in
``build/images``::

-rw-rw-r-- 1  5368460 Oct 14 15:59 redwood_x86-r0.initrd
-rw-rw-r-- 1  3121200 Sep 15 13:53 redwood_x86-r0.vmlinuz
-rw-rw-r-- 1 17825792 Sep 15 14:35 onie-recovery-x86_64-redwood_x86-r0.iso
-rw-rw-r-- 1  8521333 Sep 15 14:06 onie-updater-x86_64-redwood_x86-r0


redwood_x86-r0.vmlinuz -- This is the ONIE kernel image

redwood_x86-r0.initrd  -- This is the ONIE initramfs (filesystem)

onie-updater-x86_64-redwood_x86-r0 -- This is the ONIE self-update
image.  This image is a self-extracting archive used for installing
ONIE.

onie-recovery-x86_64-redwood_x86-r0.iso -- This is a recovery ISO image
that can be install as a CDROM image.

Cross-Compiling the DEMO OS
===========================

To compile the demo OS first change directories to ``build-config``
and then type ``"make -j12 MACHINEROOT=../machine/inventec MACHINE=redwood_x86 demo"``.
For example::

  $ cd build-config
  $ make -j4 MACHINEROOT=../machine/inventec MACHINE=redwood_x86 demo

When complete, the demo OS installer is located in ``build/images``::

-rw-rw-r-- 1 8510625 Oct 14 15:59 demo-diag-installer-x86_64-redwood_x86-r0.bin
-rw-rw-r-- 1 8510625 Oct 14 15:59 demo-installer-x86_64-redwood_x86-r0.bin

